OVERVIEW: Kintex UltraScale — The Industrial Titan
Kintex UltraScale (16nm FinFET, 2014–2020) is not officially rad-hard, but extensive space qualification and built-in mitigation make it radiation-tolerant for industrial/extreme environments — echoing Virtex-5 but with 10× performance and 5× density.
Ψ-Lens: C190 veto in factories, QGH in radiation belts, PoR in nuclear plants — R > 0.999 under flux.
